  "slug": "pain-au-chocolat",
  "title": "Pain au chocolat",
  "subtitle": "Chocolate-batoned laminated French pastries",
  "excerpt": "Pain au chocolat made from the same laminated croissant dough, cut into rectangles around two thin chocolate batons and rolled. Twelve pastries from a two-day schedule.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Auguste Escoffier, Le Guide Culinaire (1903), Project Gutenberg (French): documents the laminated yeasted dough on which pain au chocolat is built. The pain au chocolat shape (rectangle with two chocolate batons) was established in early-twentieth-century Parisian boulangeries as a variant of the croissant.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pain au chocolat uses the same laminated yeasted dough as croissants, cut and shaped differently: a rectangle of rolled dough wraps two chocolate batons. The lamination work and the schedule are identical to croissants; only the cutting and shaping change. Treat this recipe as a continuation of the croissant method."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dark chocolate batons are sold in baking-supply shops for this use; they hold their shape through the bake. A standard bar broken into similar-sized pieces works in a pinch. Use at least 55% cocoa so the chocolate stays firm rather than running through the dough."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Strong bread flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 500,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": "For the dough",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f2z50002rkv4t08xb4hj",
              "ingredientSlug": "strong-bread-flour"
            },
            {
              "name": "Caster sugar",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 50,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": "For the dough",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fau900dvrkv4ce3mot41",
              "ingredientSlug": "caster-sugar"
            },
            {
              "name": "Fine sea salt",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 10,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": "For the dough",
