            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 12
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 1: dough, butter, lamination"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mix the {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{yeast-fast-action}} in a stand mixer. Add the cold {{whole-milk}} and softened first {{unsalted-butter}}. Mix on low for 6 minutes to a smooth dough."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shape the dough into a 20x15 cm rectangle, wrap, and chill for 1 hour."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Beat the second {{unsalted-butter}} between two sheets of baking paper into a 20x15 cm rectangle. Chill for 30 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Roll the dough to 40x20 cm. Place the butter on one half and fold the other half over. Roll out to 60x20 cm and make a single fold (letter fold). Wrap and rest 30 minutes in the fridge."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Repeat the roll-and-fold twice more, resting 30 minutes between each. Chill overnight after the third fold."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 2: cut and shape with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "chocolate batons",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99c7bk0000vgv4t5a8khgo"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Roll the rested dough to a 45x30 cm rectangle, 4 mm thick. Trim the edges square. Cut into 12 rectangles, each about 11x10 cm."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place a baton of {{dark-chocolate}} along one short edge of each rectangle. Roll the dough over the baton once. Place a second baton against the first roll, then continue rolling tightly to the other end."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set seam-down on lined trays with 5 cm between each pastry."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Proof, glaze, bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Proof at warm room temperature for about 2 hours until puffed and the layers are visible from the side."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Brush the pastries with the beaten {{eggs}}."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bake at 200°C for 8 minutes, then drop to 180°C and bake for another 10 minutes. The pastries should be deep gold all over and the chocolate visible at the cut ends but not running out."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
